<doc id="175181" wikidata="Q819139" url="?curid=175181" title="Kortessem">
<text>Kortessem (; ) is a municipality located in the Belgian province of Limburg near Hasselt. On January 1, 2006, Kortessem had a total population of 8,074. The total area is 33.90 km2 which gives a population density of 238 inhabitants per km2.

The municipality consists of the following sub-municipalities: Kortessem, Guigoven, Vliermaal, Vliermaalroot, and Wintershoven.

Up until its destruction by a storm in 2009, Kortessem was the home of the &quot;Onzelievehereboom&quot;: a 1200-year-old oak.

Since 16 May 2014 Herman Van Rompuy is an honorary citizen.

